{"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Request an asynchronous write of "},{"code":"count","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" bytes from "},{"code":"buffer","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" into","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the stream. When the operation is finished "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"callback"},{"type":"text","text":" will be called."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"You can then call ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_output_stream_write_finish()"},{"type":"text","text":" to get the result of the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"operation."}],"metadata":{"externalID":"s:3GIO20OutputStreamProtocolPAAE10writeAsync6buffer5count10ioPriority11cancellable8callback8userDataySvSg_S2iAA14CancellableRefVSgySpySo8_GObjectVGSg_SpySo13_GAsyncResultVGSgAKtXCSgAKtF::SYNTHESIZED::s:3GIO15OutputStreamRefV","title":"writeAsync(buffer:count:ioPriority:cancellable:callback:userData:)","extendedModule":"GIO","symbolKind":"method","roleHeading":"Instance Method","fragments":[{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"writeAsync","kind":"identifier"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"text":"buffer","kind":"externalParam"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:Sv","text":"UnsafeMutableRawPointer","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"kind":"text","text":"!, "},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"count"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"text":"Int","preciseIdentifier":"s:Si","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"text":", ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"ioPriority"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:Si","text":"Int"},{"kind":"text","text":", "},{"text":"cancellable","kind":"externalParam"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:3GIO14CancellableRefV","text":"CancellableRef","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"kind":"text","text":"?, "},{"text":"callback","kind":"externalParam"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"GAsyncReadyCallback","preciseIdentifier":"c:@T@GAsyncReadyCallback"},{"text":"?, ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"userData"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"text":"gpointer","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"c:gtypes.h@T@gpointer"},{"kind":"text","text":"?)"}],"modules":[{"name":"GIO"}],"role":"symbol"},"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/gio\/outputstreamref\/writeasync(buffer:count:iopriority:cancellable:callback:userdata:)"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"kind":"symbol","primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"platforms":["macOS"],"tokens":[{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"writeAsync","kind":"identifier"},{"text":"(","kind":"text"},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"buffer"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"text":"UnsafeMutableRawPointer","preciseIdentifier":"s:Sv","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"text":"!, ","kind":"text"},{"text":"count","kind":"externalParam"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"text":"Int","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:Si"},{"kind":"text","text":", "},{"text":"ioPriority","kind":"externalParam"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:Si","text":"Int","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"text":", ","kind":"text"},{"text":"cancellable","kind":"externalParam"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/CancellableRef","preciseIdentifier":"s:3GIO14CancellableRefV","kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"CancellableRef"},{"text":"? = nil, ","kind":"text"},{"text":"callback","kind":"externalParam"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"c:@T@GAsyncReadyCallback","text":"GAsyncReadyCallback"},{"text":"? = nil, ","kind":"text"},{"text":"userData","kind":"externalParam"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"text":"gpointer","preciseIdentifier":"c:gtypes.h@T@gpointer","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"kind":"text","text":"? = nil)"}],"languages":["swift"]}],"kind":"declarations"},{"content":[{"anchor":"discussion","text":"Discussion","level":2,"type":"heading"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"During an async request no other sync and async calls are allowed,"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"and will result in ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"pending"},{"text":" errors.","type":"text"}]},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"A value of ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"count"},{"text":" larger than ","type":"text"},{"code":"G_MAXSSIZE","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" will cause a","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"invalidArgument"},{"text":" error.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"On success, the number of bytes written will be passed to the","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"code":"callback","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":". It is not an error if this is not the same as the"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"requested size, as it can happen e.g. on a partial I\/O error,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"but generally we try to write as many bytes as requested."}]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"You are guaranteed that this method will never fail with"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"wouldBlock"},{"type":"text","text":" - if "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"stream"},{"type":"text","text":" can’t accept more data, the"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"method will just wait until this changes.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Any outstanding I\/O request with higher priority (lower numerical","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"value) will be executed before an outstanding request with lower","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"priority. Default priority is [PRIORITY_DEFAULT](\/\/documentation\/glib\/priority_default.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"The asynchronous methods have a default fallback that uses threads","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"to implement asynchronicity, so they are optional for inheriting","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"classes. However, if you override one you must override all."}]},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"For the synchronous, blocking version of this function, see","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_output_stream_write()"},{"type":"text","text":"."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Note that no copy of "},{"code":"buffer","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" will be made, so it must stay valid","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"until "},{"code":"callback","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" is called. See "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_output_stream_write_bytes_async()"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"for a [Bytes](\/\/documentation\/glib\/bytes version that will automatically hold a reference to","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"the contents (without copying) for the duration of the call."}],"type":"paragraph"}],"kind":"content"}],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/OutputStreamRef","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/OutputStreamRef\/OutputStreamProtocol-Implementations"]]},"schemaVersion":{"patch":0,"major":0,"minor":3},"sections":[],"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/OutputStreamRef\/writeAsync(buffer:count:ioPriority:cancellable:callback:userData:)","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"references":{"doc://GIO/documentation/GIO/OutputStreamRef":{"abstract":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GOutputStream"},{"type":"text","text":" is a base class for implementing streaming output."}],"title":"OutputStreamRef","fragments":[{"text":"struct","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"OutputStreamRef","kind":"identifier"}],"identifier":"do